A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and celebrating Chelsea Rathburn as the distinguished Poet Laureate of
2 Georgia; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Chelsea Rathburn has long been recognized by the citizens of this state for her
4 critically acclaimed poetry and creative collections, having been appointed as Poet Laureate
5 of the State of Georgia in 2019 and serving as an ambassador for poetry and a champion of
6 the literary arts in Georgia; and
7 WHEREAS, born in Jacksonville and raised in Miami, Florida, Chelsea Rathburn has deep
8 roots in the State of Georgia, where her mother's family has lived since the 1830s; and
9 WHEREAS, Rathburn holds a B.A. from Florida State University and an M.F.A. from the
10 University of Arkansas. Rathburn moved to Young Harris from Decatur, Georgia, where she
11 taught poetry workshops at Emory University and chaired the poetry track for the Decatur
12 Book Festival; and
13 WHEREAS, Chelsea Rathburn now lives in Young Harris, Georgia, with her husband, the
14 poet James Davis May, and their daughter; Chelsea Rathburn is currently an associate
15 professor of English-Creative Writing at Mercer University; and
